<subSubSection id="C368652E935D8E00F2FAFA76FC43F945" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935D8E00F2FAFA76FC43F945" blockId="4.[151,1437,1436,1679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">
At present there are five subspecies within 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F092FA77FC02FA35" authority="(Wrase, 2011)" baseAuthorityName="Wrase" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[687,979,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cupreus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F092FA77FCFBFA35" box="[687,810,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">H. cupreus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F104FA76FC1DFA35" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[825,972,1508,1534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" refId="ref12634" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2011) Genus Tschitscherinellus. Arndt, E., Schnitter, P., Sfenthourakis, S. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (Eds.), Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia, pp. 163." type="book" year="2011">Wrase, 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935D8E00F625FA76FBAEFA35" box="[1048,1151,1508,1534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">lectotype</typeStatus>
likely corresponds to the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F32BF99AFCF5F9E9" authority="Faldermann, 1836" authorityName="Faldermann" authorityYear="1836" box="[278,804,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cupreus" subSpecies="fastuosus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F32BF99AFD9FF9E9" box="[278,590,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Harpalus cupreus fastuosus</emphasis>
Faldermann, 1836
</taxonomicName>
, distributed in Central and Eastern Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935D8E00F731F99AFABDF9E9" box="[1292,1388,1544,1570]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
and the Levant (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F320F9BEFDE1F98D" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[285,560,1580,1607]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" pagination="1810" refId="ref11718" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 c) Subtribe Harpalina Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 515 - 562." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017c</bibRefCitation>
). A probable relict population exists in Middle Atlas (
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F6B1F9BFFECBF9A1" authority="Antoine, 1941" authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cupreus" subSpecies="asaphus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F6B1F9BFFABBF98D" box="[1164,1386,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">H. cupreus asaphus</emphasis>
Antoine, 1941
</taxonomicName>
). This European Mediterranean species may be distinguished from the related 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935D8E00F6ADF9C2FE99F945" authority="Wrase et Kataev, 2011" authorityName="Wrase et Kataev" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935D8E00F6ADF9C2FA9FF9A1" box="[1168,1358,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="488">Harpalus reitteri</emphasis>
Wrase et Kataev, 2011
</taxonomicName>
, distributed in the Balkans, following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935D8E00F0CEF9E7FC5CF945" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[755,909,1652,1679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="488" refId="ref12634" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2011) Genus Tschitscherinellus. Arndt, E., Schnitter, P., Sfenthourakis, S. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (Eds.), Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia, pp. 163." type="book" year="2011">Wrase (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
